<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Automation on jogi-writes</title><link>https://karuneshb.github.io/jogi-writes/posts/automation/</link><description>Recent content in Automation on jogi-writes</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en-us</language><atom:link href="https://karuneshb.github.io/jogi-writes/posts/automation/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Automating Tasks and System Monitoring with Linux Scripts</title><link>https://karuneshb.github.io/jogi-writes/posts/automation/automating-tasks-and-system-monitoring-with-linux-scripts/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://karuneshb.github.io/jogi-writes/posts/automation/automating-tasks-and-system-monitoring-with-linux-scripts/</guid><description>&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h1 id="script-1-task-automation"&gt;Script 1: Task Automation&lt;a class="anchor" href="#script-1-task-automation"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Source Code:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;#!/bin/bash
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;user&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;$(&lt;/span&gt;whoami&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;#Takes the name of the current user for greeting&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;echo &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Hi, &lt;/span&gt;$user&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;echo &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;this is a system updater script...&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;sleep 0.5
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;sudo apt-get update
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;echo &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;checking for updates done successfully&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;sleep 0.5
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;sudo apt-get upgrade -y
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;echo &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;updates installed successfully&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Problem Solved: Automates updates to the system to save time.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Rationale: Manually entering the commands is time taking. This script helps with that. Prospectively, this could be executed right after the user is logged in to the system.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>BASH Scripting</title><link>https://karuneshb.github.io/jogi-writes/posts/automation/bash-scripting/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://karuneshb.github.io/jogi-writes/posts/automation/bash-scripting/</guid><description>&lt;h3 id="getting-started-with-the-bash-scripting"&gt;Getting started with the bash scripting&lt;a class="anchor" href="#getting-started-with-the-bash-scripting"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Run the command to know which shell/script is being used.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;~$ which $SHELL
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;/usr/bin/zsh&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Use the “echo” command to display a message, like&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;~$ echo &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Hello World&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Hello World&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Create a file, and name it like name.sh. After a file is created, it will be automatically opened. If not then type &lt;em&gt;nano name.sh&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Start typing the script in the text editor. After you are done, type &lt;em&gt;Ctrl+X&lt;/em&gt;, &lt;em&gt;y/Y&lt;/em&gt; then hit Enter.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>